{
  "texts": [
    "The behaviour of algorithms, and machine-learning algorithms in particular, is difficult to predict and good intentions are insufficient to ensure a working algorithm [c.f.",
    "the failure of hundreds of machinelearning algorithms developed to diagnose covid, Heaven (2021) ].",
    "As discussed above, steps to improve explainability and fairness also don't guarantee outcomes that we find acceptable, if we don't know what their effectiveness was or which trade-offs were made.",
    "Ultimately, one has to trust that the developers saw outcomes that they deemed acceptable, rather than that one is able to determine for oneself whether this kind of algorithm is justified for this kind of goal.",
    "As such, important information is missing to establish legitimacy."
  ]
}